                <note rend="inline" type="source">393.1111 Nelson, Bert N./59: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-02-02T13:00:00+08:00"
                            >February 2, 1931—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received February 2—9:30 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>50. Legation’s 49, January 31, 1 p.m. Following has been sent to the American
                    Consul at Nanking: <pb facs="1047" n="937" xml:id="pg_937"/>
                    <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“February 2, 1 p.m. Following from Hankow repeated for your information:
                                <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>‘January 31, 1 p.m. I made a personal appeal to Mayor Liu Wen-tao
                                    this morning to telegraph General Chiang Kai-shek and suggested
                                    that he issue peremptory instructions to the military commander
                                    in the Changhsikang area to effect the early release of Nelson,
                                    failing which the commander will be held personally responsible.
                                    The Mayor promised to despatch such a telegram to General Chiang
                                    at once.’”</p>
                            </quote>
                        </p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
